tafsir[5]{c,v,t}:
  37,33,"So the followers and the leaders will share in the punishment on the Day of Judgement; none will benefit the other in any way because they were all partners in deviance and disbelief in the world."
  37,38,"O idolaters! You are surely going to suffer the painful punishment on the Day of Judgement due to your disbelief and rejection of the messengers."
  37,39,"O idolaters! Your requital will only be for the disbelief and sins you used to commit in the world."
  37,42,"From this special provision will be that they are provided with the purest of fruits they ever eat and desire; on top of that they will be honoured with their ranks being raised and being able to see the blessed face of Allah."
  37,44,"They will lean on thrones opposite to and facing one another; each one happy to meet his brother."